run().details: To deploy contracts on $chainName Make sure "./script/configs/Messaging003.dc.json" exists, then call forge script script/DeployMessaging003<?>.s.sol -f chainName --ffi --broadcast Note: Verification will not natively work, need to verify externally

runDry().details: To simulate deployment on $chainName forge script script/DeployMessaging003<?>.s.sol -f chainName --sig "runDry()"

sortJSON(string).details: Reads JSON from given path, sorts its keys and overwrites the file.

testScript().details: Function to exclude script from coverage report

artifactPath(string).notice: Returns path to the contract artifact.

createDir(string).notice: Create directory if it not exists already

deployConfigExists(string).notice: Checks if deploy config exists for a given contract on the current chain.

deployConfigFn(string).notice: Returns deploy config filename for the contract.

deployConfigPath(string).notice: Returns path to the contract deploy config JSON on the current chain.

deploymentFn(string).notice: Returns deployment filename for the contract.

deploymentPath(string).notice: Returns path to the contract deployment for the current chain.

getChainAlias().notice: Returns name of the current chain.

globalDeployConfigPath(string).notice: Returns path to the global contract deploy config JSON.

loadDeployConfig(string).notice: Loads deploy config for a given contract on the current chain. Will revert if config doesn't exist.

loadDeployment(string).notice: Returns the deployment for a contract on the current chain, if it exists. Reverts if it doesn't exist.

loadGlobalDeployConfig(string).notice: Loads deploy config for a given contract on the current chain. Will revert if config doesn't exist.

run().notice: Main function with the deploy logic.

runDry().notice: Function to simulate the deployment procedure.

saveDeployConfig(string,string).notice: Saves deploy config for a given contract on the current chain.

saveDeployment(string,string,address,byt.notice: Saves the deployment JSON for a deployed contract.

testDeployerUtils().notice: Prevents this contract from being included in the coverage report

tryLoadDeployment(string).notice: Returns the deployment for a contract on the current chain, if it exists. Returns address(0), if it doesn't exist.

documentation.text: @dev Function to exclude script from coverage report

@dev Deploys Messaging contracts, transfer ownership and sanity check the new deployments.
 Will save the deployments, if script is being broadcasted.

typeDescriptions.typeString: function (string memory,function () returns (address,bytes memory),function (address)) returns (address,bytes memory)

documentation.text:
@dev Deploys BondingManager or LightManager
 Note: requires Origin, Destination, StatementInbox (and Summit for BondingManager) addresses to be set

@dev Deploys Inbox or LightInbox
 Note: requires AgentManager, Origin, Destination (and Summit for Inbox) addresses to be set
@dev Adds agents to BondingManager (no-op for LightManager)

@dev Deploys GasOracle.
 Note: requires Destination address to have been set.

@dev Deploys Origin.
 Note: requires AgentManager, StatementInbox and GasOracle addresses to have been set.

@dev Deploys Summit.
 Note: requires AgentManager and StatementInbox addresses to have been set.
@dev Transfers ownership of contracts to the owner defined in the global config.
@dev Transfers ownership of a given contract to a new owner.

@dev Checks that all agents have been added correctly to BondingManager
 or that they could be added to LightManager.
@dev Checks that all contracts have been deployed and initialized correctly
